<!-- Custom CSS for the Emergency Response page -->
<style>
    .vision-mission-image {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        overflow: hidden;
        height: 500px; /* Adjust the height as needed */
    }

    .vision-mission-img {
        position: absolute;
        top: 10%;
        left: 50%;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    }

    .vision-mission-content {
        max-width: 1200px; /* Adjust max-width as needed */
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #ffffff; /* Example background color */
        color: #2f4507; /* Example text color */
    }

    .vision-mission-content h1, .vision-mission-content h2, .vision-mission-content h3 {
        color: #2f4507;
    }

    .vision-mission-content h1 {
        margin-bottom: 30px; /* Increase space below h1 */
    }

    .vision-mission-content h2 {
        margin-top: 30px; /* Increase space above h2 */
        margin-bottom: 20px; /* Adjust space below h2 if needed */
    }

    .vision-mission-content p, .vision-mission-content ul {
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .vision-mission-content ul {
        list-style-type: disc;
        padding-left: 20px;
    }

    /* New styling for the content blocks */
    .content-blocks {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 40px; /* Space between main content and blocks */
    }

    .content-block {
        background-color: #f7f7f7; /* Light grey background */
        border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; /* Light border */
        border-radius: 10px; /* Rounded corners */
        width: 48%; /* Two blocks side by side */
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        padding: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); /* Subtle shadow for depth */
    }

    .content-block img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        border-radius: 10px; /* Match image corners to block */
    }

    .content-block h2 {
        color: #2f4507;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .content-block p {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333333; /* Darker text for readability */
    }
</style>

<!-- Image Section -->
<div class="vision-mission-image">
    <img src="18.jpg" alt="Emergency Response Image" class="vision-mission-img">
</div>

<!-- Content Section -->
<div class="vision-mission-content">
    <h1 style="text-align: center;">EMERGENCY RESPONSE</h1>
    <br>
    <p>MFH is committed to delivering essential support and accurate information to the most remote villages in Uttarakhand and Himachal Pradesh during emergencies. By leveraging a network of local partners, we ensure last-mile coverage and effective disaster response, including gathering vital data and coordinating with national and international agencies for both immediate relief and long-term recovery. Our resource generation strategy is driven by community needs assessments, enabling swift mobilization of supplies, securing funding for recovery, and building resilience. We ensure rapid deployment through pre-established logistical networks and trained local volunteers, addressing urgent needs with precision. Our relief distribution adheres to international standards, focusing on the most vulnerable populations and ensuring aid is delivered efficiently, transparently, and with respect for recipients' dignity.</p>

    <!-- Blocks Section -->
    <div class="content-blocks">
        <!-- Block 1 -->
        <div class="content-block">
            <img src="block1.jpg" alt="Coordination Image">
            <h2>Coordination among various stakeholders</h2>
            <p>MFH plays a pivotal role in coordinating among various stakeholders during emergencies, ensuring a streamlined and efficient response. As a central hub for communication and collaboration, MFH unites government agencies, local partners, international organizations, and community groups to harmonize efforts and optimize resource allocation. By establishing clear protocols and maintaining active dialogue, we effectively manage relief distribution, avoiding duplication and ensuring that aid reaches all affected populations equitably. Our strategic coordination helps to prevent overlaps and gaps in assistance, maximizing the impact of every resource and enhancing the overall effectiveness of the emergency response. MFHâ€™s strong partnership with Sphere India at both the national and state levels further strengthens our coordination efforts. Through meticulous planning and robust collaborations with inter-agency groups at state and district levels, MFH ensures that relief efforts are well-coordinated, transparent, and focused on addressing the urgent needs of disaster-affected communities.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Block 2 -->
        <div class="content-block">
            <img src="block2.jpg" alt="Protection and Dignity Image">
            <h2>Ensuring Protection and Dignity During Disasters</h2>
            <p>MFH is deeply committed to ensuring the protection of vulnerable populations, including children, the elderly, and women, during disasters. Our approach integrates robust safeguarding measures to prevent exploitation and abuse, including anti-child trafficking initiatives. We implement child protection protocols, provide safe spaces, and support mental health services to address trauma and ensure the well-being of young survivors. For the elderly and women, MFH focuses on creating safe environments and offering tailored support to meet their specific needs, ensuring they are protected from harm and have access to essential services. By coordinating with local authorities, international organizations, and community groups, MFH actively works to identify and address risks, ensuring that all relief efforts prioritize the safety and dignity of those most at risk.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

